# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb
Cargo.lock.bak

# insta snapshot pending files
**/*.pending-snap
**/.*.pending-snap

# mdBook
/docs/book
/docs/.mdbook-cache

# Coverage
/lcov.info
/coverage/
*.profraw
*.profdata

# cargo-mutants run output (F98)
/mutants.out
/mutants.out.old

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.iml

# Agent-specific working files (not tracked by default)
.agent/scratch/
.agent/local.md

# Python (scripts/)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Local-only scratch space (see examples/local/README.md)
/examples/local/*
!/examples/local/README.md

# Raw git-cloned upstreams under examples/public/ — the fetcher
# shallow-clones upstream repos into `raw/` subdirectories; the
# committable material is the adjacent `source.yaml` plus any
# per-source adapter output (F81). The raw clones themselves are
# reproducible from the URLs in `source.yaml` and must not ship.
/examples/public/**/raw/

# Raw HTML dumps from the HTTP-fetch path — the committable triplet
# is `source.yaml` + `clean.html` + `content.md` (metadata,
# chrome-stripped HTML, and markdown derivative). `raw.html` is the
# pre-clean reference used when debugging the cleaner; one FR source
# (rgaa-4-1) is ~950 KB on its own, and the batch as a whole makes
# git history noisy. Re-run `just texts-fetch` to regenerate locally.
/examples/public/**/raw.html

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Windows
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Linux
*~

# Env
.env
.env.local

# Logs
*.log

# Generated docs
/target/doc
